article.headline: Portland State 95, Evergreen State 76
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Juma Kamara scored 20 points as Portland State followed its win over Arizona State with a 95-76 victory over Evergreen State on Monday. Scott Morrison added 15 points and 14 rebounds for the Vikings (3-2). Adam Moore led Evergreen State (2-2) with 32 points, and Greg Shadowvine added 22 for the NAIA Geoducks. The Vikings struggled early, but managed to find their rhythm from long range -- hitting 6-of-10 3-pointers in the first half. The Vikings then took control with their inside strength, outrebounding the Geoducks 50-28 on the night and amassing a 38-16 advantage in points in the paint. Portland State used a 20-5 run at the end of the first half and beginning of the second half to put the game out of reach. A rebound dunk by Morrison with 15:56 left to play put the Vikings on top 57-37. Julius Thomas had 11 points for the Vikings and guard Ryan Sommer had eight assists and five steals.
